-- 2010-10-28T03:59:59Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-28/ciech-fortuna-pbg-may-be-active-today-central-european-equity-preview.html
The following is a list of companies
whose shares may have unusual price changes in central European
markets. Stock symbols are in parentheses after company names.
Share prices are from the last close.  Poland’s  WIG20 Index  gained 0.5 percent, the Czech  PX Index 
climbed 0.8 percent and Hungary’s  BUX Index  fell 1.1 percent.  Ciech SA  (CIE PW): Shareholders of Poland’s biggest
chemical group are scheduled to meet to vote on a capital
increase. Ciech declined 1.4 percent to 19.79 zloty.  Fortuna Entertainment Group NV  (FEG PW): The Czech betting
company will start trading on the Warsaw Stock Exchange.  PBG SA  (PBG PW): Poland’s largest construction company by
market value is analyzing the sale of builder PNI Sp. z o.o.
started this week by state railroad PKP SA. PBG shares rose 0.3
percent to 220.8 zloty.  To contact the reporters on this story:
